      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of COU operating conditions including at least two load levels and two specimen orientations relevant to in vivo loading.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed exclusively under the ASTM F1717 standard protocol: single quasi-static ramp to failure at 1 mm/min, room temperature, single construct orientation. No variation in load rate, temperature, or orientation was explored. The COU encompasses only the F1717 standardized condition, so this single-condition limitation is acknowledged but not fully mitigated. Achieved Gradation 2 against a Gradation 3 requirement — this shortfall is noted in the decision record."
    },
