      "rationale": "The three QoIs — construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement — are the primary endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and directly correspond to clinical performance requirements for pedicle screw fixation (rigidity, fatigue resistance, and post-yield energy absorption). QoI relevance confirmed by clinical affairs review."
